# Edit workflow

- For any non-trivial change (multiple files, migrations, UI passes, or sequential steps), **start by writing a short todo list** of the concrete edits or steps, then work through and mark items done as you go.
- Prefer one todo item per meaningful unit of work (e.g. one feature slice, one view, one migration) rather than a single vague “fix everything” item.
- Keep the list updated so remaining work is obvious if the session stops mid-way.

# Tailwind CSS — responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)

This project uses **Tailwind v4** (`tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/vite`). Style **mobile first**: base classes = smallest screens; add breakpoints for larger viewports.

## Breakpoints (default)

| Prefix | Min width | Typical use |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| (none) | 0 | Mobile — default layout, typography, spacing |
| `sm:` | 640px | Large phones / small tablets |
| `md:` | 768px | **Tablet** — adjust grids, nav, padding |
| `lg:` | 1024px | **Desktop** — multi-column layouts, sidebars |
| `xl:` | 1280px | Wide desktop refinements |
| `2xl:` | 1536px | Extra-wide only when needed |

## Patterns

- **Layout**: stack on mobile, row on tablet/desktop.

```html
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 md:flex-row md:gap-6 lg:gap-8">
```

- **Typography**: readable base size; scale up on larger screens.

```html
<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl">
<p class="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">
```

- **Spacing**: tighter on mobile, roomier on desktop.

```html
<section class="px-4 py-6 md:px-6 md:py-10 lg:px-8 lg:py-12">
```

- **Grids**: one column mobile, more columns as width grows.

```html
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
```

- **Show/hide by breakpoint** (use sparingly; prefer one responsive layout when possible):

```html
<button class="md:hidden">Menu</button>
<nav class="hidden md:flex">
```

## Rules of thumb

- Do not design **only** for desktop; verify **mobile → tablet → desktop** in that order.
- Avoid fixed pixel widths for whole layouts; prefer `max-w-*`, `w-full`, flex/grid, and fluid spacing.
- Reuse consistent spacing/typography scales across Blade and any JS-rendered UI.
